claim.claim-text:
A rotary actuator (20, 200) comprising:
a plurality of ball bearings (42);
an outer cylinder (26) having multiple fluid ports (41) each configured to admit fluid pressure from a fluid pressure supply (15);
a piston (24, 124, 224) circumscribed by the outer cylinder (26), wherein the piston, the outer cylinder, and the plurality of ball bearings collectively form an outer ball screw (29-O), and wherein the piston is configured to translate along a longitudinal center axis (A20) of the rotary actuator in response to the fluid pressure; and
an inner shaft (25) circumscribed by the piston (24), wherein the inner shaft, the piston, and the plurality of ball bearings collectively form an inner ball screw (29-1) that is concentric with the outer ball screw about the longitudinal center axis;
wherein the outer ball screw and the inner ball screw together form an interlaced ball circuit (50) having one or more shared ball paths (40), and wherein translation of the piston along the longitudinal center axis in response to the fluid pressure is operative to rotate the piston and the inner shaft, and to thereby recirculate the plurality of ball bearings between the outer ball screw and the inner ball screw through the interlaced ball circuit.

A fixed-wing aircraft (10) comprising:
a fuselage (16);
a pair of wings (12) connected to the fuselage;
an empennage (14) connected to the fuselage;
an aerodynamic flight control panel (18) connected to one of the wings and/or to the empennage via a revolute hinged joint (21) having an axis of rotation; and
a rotary actuator (20, 200) connected to the revolute hinged joint, including:
a rotatable inner shaft (25) connected to the axis of rotation;
a piston (24, 124, 224) circumscribing the rotatable inner shaft, and configured to translate along a longitudinal center axis of the rotary actuator in response to fluid pressure,
an outer cylinder (26) circumscribing the piston and having multiple fluid ports (41) configured to admit the fluid pressure, wherein the rotatable inner shaft, the piston, and the outer cylinder are concentrically arranged with respect to the longitudinal center axis (A20) to form two concentric ball screws (29) that together define an interlaced ball circuit (50) having at least one shared ball path, wherein the piston is configured to separate the outer cylinder into multiple pressure cavities (30A, 30B), and the multiple fluid ports are configured to connect the fluid pressure supply (15) to the multiple pressure cavities; and
a plurality of ball bearings (42) positioned within the at least one shared ball path of the interlaced ball circuit, wherein translation of the piston along the longitudinal center axis in response to admission of the fluid pressure into the outer cylinder is operative to recirculate the plurality of ball bearings between the two concentric ball screws via the at least one shared ball path, and to rotate the piston and the inner shaft to thereby actuate the revolute hinged joint and change an angular position of the aerodynamic flight control panel.
